<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 95-13-05 - Shuttle Shifting</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi951305" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>95-13-05</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>December, 1995</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>TRANSMISSION</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Shuttle Shifting</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>1000</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4000</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>Medium duty vehicles with an Allison AT or MT automatic transmission and with a T 444E or DT 466E
                    engine may experience undesirable transmission shuttle shifting. Navistar offers an alternate Engine
                    Control Module (ECM) or a KDS box (depending on when the vehicle was built) to correct this
                    condition if you experience a complaint of this nature. The replacement ECM's do not require any
                    changes to the engine control system programming. The following table lists build dates, engine and
                    the type of modification that is required (along with part numbers) to correct the shuttle shifting
                    condition.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
